cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the tradeoff between privacy and utility in terms of mutual information, which is a core concept in information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the paper also discusses privacy leakage and private information contained in observable data, it could also fit into cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper's focus on quantifying privacy and utility tradeoffs could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
